data.content:
Yes — MSTest v3+ supports **ValueTuples** with `DynamicData`, eliminating the `object[]` boxing:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[DynamicData(nameof(TestData))]
public void Validate_ReturnsExpected(string input, bool expected)
{
    var result = Validator.IsValid(input);
    Assert.AreEqual(expected, result);
}

public static IEnumerable<(string Input, bool Expected)> TestData =>
[
    ("valid@email.com", true),
    ("invalid", false),
    ("", false),
];
```

**What changed:**
- `IEnumerable<object[]>` → `IEnumerable<(string, bool)>` — compile-time type safety, no casts
- Array syntax `["a", true]` → tuple syntax `("a", true)`

The test method signature stays the same. MSTest automatically destructures the tuple into the method parameters. Requires **MSTest 3.4+**.
